# Testing

Stack: **Jest** + **Supertest** (not Vitest).

## What to test

- HTTP integration: routes + middleware + error shapes
- Service business logic (critical auth flows)
- Validation schemas (edge cases)

## Integration pattern

```typescript
describe("GET /api/v1/health", () => {
  it("returns 200 when DB connected", async () => {
    const res = await request(app).get("/api/v1/health");
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    expect(res.body.success).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

## Auth tests

- 401 without token
- 403 wrong role
- 400 invalid body (Zod)

## Prisma in tests

- Prefer integration tests against test DB for Prisma paths
- Mock Prisma only for isolated unit tests
- Never run tests against production `DATABASE_URL`

## Commands

```bash
npm test
npm run test:watch
```

Run tests before claiming success. No trivial `expect(true).toBe(true)` tests.
